    "Precision of extraction of the event's date (temporal factor) was 87.7%.",
    "When considering unique events per patient, this rate translates to 380 patients with one or more events and 5,344 patients with no events (Table 2).The effect of stressful life events and selected demographic variables on cancer screening adherence was evaluated using a logistic regression model.",
    "The odds ratios of being screened, sorted by the lowest p-value first are presented in Fig. 1.",
    "The regression table can be found in Supplement D (Table 3).",
    "Being White or Caucasian race reduces the odds of screening (OR 0.64 95% CI 0.57-0.73), along with belonging to other races (OR 0.76 95% CI 0.54-1.05)."
